column5: Slooooow drift with a Lindy rig. Extremely light bite. My best results are the last hour before dark. Know your slot size.
Walleye are still deep but moving in. Start around 22-25 fow and move in from 5:30 till dark. Worms are still catching lots of fish.
slash baits in the early am and at dusk..  twister tails tipped with worms on a sloowww crank.  good luck!
I'm heading to Lakair  tomorrow (Tuesday) in search of a few BIG fall muskies.
HWY 64 Bridge area was a a good place to catch them.
I had good luck fishing neck-down areas between islands, or islands and the mainland provided there was deepish water (>10ft) between.
Lew ..how long are ya staying ...Id like to get lil momma into a Muskie up there Sat

Some very good advice above. Like others, most of my fishing is done in narrows lindy rigging. Set your trolling motor to the slowest speed possible that will keep the boat moving. White, orange and pink are my go to jig colours, white being the preferred. Good luck.

I'm already home Darrell, it was just a quick trip for a change of scenery.  I fished 5 hours Tuesday & all day yesterday but things were pretty quiet with just a mid 40's musky and a few pike.  Water is quite cloudy compared to only a month ago with visibility about 3 feet and temps range from high 50's to low 60's.  Sorry I'm gonna miss you guys but good luck and enjoy your trip.

Lew...was looking forward to meeting you there...ill bring the Muskie gear as well see what happens trolling for a few hours...if you ever wanna come Fish Georgian Bay in Britt here..I'm game ,,I got a lil spotted ski Saturday evening  and a 42 inch last night ...ill let you know the outcome this weekend
Heading there this weekend for the first time, hope the fishing is good.  The above info is great, what about bass?  Any tips for smallies.

we fished most of Saturday...then back out till dark Saturday evening..it was Beautiful out there ,,sunny and hot,,we drifted..we trolled..we casted...and we jigged...it was a tough fish for everyone there..we got Pike during the day and a few bass...Sunday we went out till 1 pm..no luck..
